Second pereiopod (
Fig. 12b
): Long and slender. Dactylus 1.1–1.3 × long as palm of propodus. Chela 2.9–3.2 × long as broad. Slender carpus 4.5–5.5 × long as broad.

First male pleopod (
Fig. 12g , h
): endopod 0.6–0.8 × exopod, with short appendix interna. Endopod with closely arranged long stalked setae on outer margin and with shorter setae on inner margin.

First female pleopod (
Fig. 12i , j
): almost equal in length to exopod 0.8–1.00 × exopod.

Preanal carina (
Fig. 13g
): shaped like protruding peg without spines and adorned with long setae.
